3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates DOGE/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium index. The exchange applies a dampening mechanism that caps extreme rates at ±2.5% per funding period. Funding payments are automatically debited or credited to perpetual contract positions based on the rate direction and position size."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","DOGE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE perpetuals exhibit some of the most volatile funding rates in the market due to retail sentiment swings and social media influence. The pair's high trading volume on Bitget ensures sufficient liquidity for large arbitrage positions, while the meme coin's price volatility creates frequent funding rate dislocations."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE/USDT funding rates on Bitget have shown extreme swings ranging from -1.5% to +2.2% during major market events. Bull market periods typically see sustained positive rates as retail traders heavily long DOGE perpetuals. Social media catalysts like Elon Musk tweets can trigger immediate funding spikes that persist for 24-48 hours. Weekend periods often show reduced funding volatility as institutional activity decreases."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable DOGE funding arbitrage occurs during community-driven pump phases when perpetual premiums spike above +1%. Bitget's copy trading feature creates additional funding pressure as popular traders' positions are replicated across thousands of followers. Cross-exchange arbitrage with lower-fee venues becomes attractive when Bitget's funding exceeds 0.5% while maintaining sufficient liquidity depth."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE's meme coin nature introduces unique risks including sudden sentiment reversals that can cause rapid funding normalization. Bitget's relatively newer market presence means lower overall liquidity compared to tier-1 exchanges during extreme volatility. The 8-hour funding interval requires careful position timing as DOGE can experience significant price moves within single funding periods that offset arbitrage gains."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical DOGE/USDT funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"DOGE funding rates on Bitget typically range from -0.2% to +0.5% during normal market conditions. However, during meme coin rallies or major social media events, rates can spike to +1.5% or higher as retail traders pile into long positions."},{"question":"How does Bitget's copy trading affect DOGE funding rates?","answer":"Copy trading amplifies funding rate movements on Bitget as popular traders' DOGE positions are automatically replicated by thousands of followers. This creates concentrated directional pressure that can sustain elevated funding rates longer than on exchanges without copy trading features."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for DOGE funding arbitrage on Bitget?","answer":"Bitget requires a minimum of 1 DOGE for perpetual contracts, but profitable funding arbitrage typically requires positions of at least $10,000 to offset trading fees and slippage. The exchange's 0.02% maker fees make smaller positions less economically viable."},{"question":"How quickly can I exit a DOGE funding arbitrage position on Bitget?","answer":"DOGE/USDT maintains good liquidity on Bitget with typical market depth allowing exits of up to $500,000 within 2-3% slippage. However, during extreme volatility or funding rate events, liquidity can thin significantly requiring more careful exit timing."}]}]
